  "title": "MARKETING MANAGER",
  "description": "<p>Marketing Manager Job Description</p><p>We are seeking an innovative marketing manager to promote our company's brand and services. In this role, you will be optimizing our marketing strategies, managing the marketing department's budget and staff, as well as preparing forecasts.</p><p>To ensure success, you will need extensive knowledge of marketing strategies and the ability to identify new business leads. An outstanding marketing manager will be someone whose expertise translates into increased brand awareness and profitability.</p><p>Marketing Manager Responsibilities</p><p>•\tEvaluating and optimizing marketing and pricing strategies.</p><p>•\tAnalyzing market trends and preparing forecasts.</p><p>•\tGenerating new business leads.</p><p>•\tDevelop strategies and tactics to get the word out about our company and drive qualified traffic to our front door</p><p>•\tDeploy successful marketing campaigns and own their implementation from ideation to execution</p><p>•\tExperiment with a variety of organic and paid acquisition channels like content creation, content curation, pay per click campaigns, event management, publicity, social media, lead generation campaigns, copywriting, performance analysis</p><p>•\tProduce valuable and engaging content for our website and blog that attracts and converts our target groupsS</p><p>•\tBuild strategic relationships and partner with key industry players, agencies and vendors</p><p>•\tPrepare and monitor the marketing budget on a quarterly and annual basis and allocate funds wisely</p><p>•\tOversee and approve marketing material, from website banners to hard copy brochures and case studies</p><p>•\tMeasure and report on the performance of marketing campaigns, gain insight and assess against goals</p><p>•\tAnalyze consumer behavior and adjust email and advertising campaigns accordingly</p><p>Marketing Manager Requirements</p><p>•\tA Bachelor’s degree in marketing, business or any other relevant field</p><p>•\tSound understanding of marketing fundamentals and tactics</p><p>•\tCreative thinking and problem-solving ability</p><p>•\tLeadership and project management skills</p><p>•\tKnowledge of digital marketing and social media marketing strategies</p><p>•\tExcellent verbal and non-verbal communication skills</p><p>•\tProficiency with marketing tools and software</p><p>•\tProficient in marketing research and statistical analysis</p><p>•\tThe ability to work under pressure.</p><p>•\tAvailability to work within opening hours (e.g. evenings, holidays, weekends).</p><p></p><p></p>",
